To use Redis as a token store simply you just have to enable it in you configuration.

You have to have the grails redis plugin installed in order to be able to use the redis as your token store.

{table}
*Config key*                                                            | *Default value*
@grails.plugin.springsecurity.rest.token.storage.useRedis@          | @false@
@grails.plugin.springsecurity.rest.token.storage.redis.expiration@  | @3600@
{table}

